-- IG Metall Says BMW Should Cut Temporary Work, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2012-02-19T19:10:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-19/ig-metall-says-bmw-should-cut-temporary-work-handelsblatt-says.html
Germany ’s IG Metall metalworkers
union said  Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  should limit temporary
work, Handelsblatt reported, citing Horst Lischka, a union
official who sits on the carmaker’s supervisory board.  BMW declined to give the exact number of temporary workers
it employs, Handelsblatt said. “Temporary work is an important
instrument to maintain flexibility,” Handelsblatt cited an
unidentified BMW spokesman as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
